name: PCI
title: PCI
purpose: (Clinical Focus: This set of values contains a procedure used to define percutaneous coronary intervention (PCI).),(Data Element Scope: The intent of this data element is to identify patients who had percutaneous coronary intervention (PCI) during an episode of acute myocardial infarction. Using the Quality Data Model, this particular element would map to the Procedure, Performed data type.),(Inclusion Criteria: Include codes that describe percutaneous transluminal coronary angioplasty.),(Exclusion Criteria: Exclude procedures and interventions that do not describe percutaneous transluminal coronary angioplasty or stent placement during an episode of acute myocardial infarction.)
